Orlando Pirates fans voiced their frustration at the lack of progress made in Senzo Meyiwa's murder case. SOWETO - A group of Orlando Pirates fans marched to the Vosloorus police department today to hand over a memorandum to the station commander. Today marks two years since the death of Bafana Bafana goalkeeper Senzo Meyiwa, yet no arrests have been made. Orlando Pirates fans voiced their frustration at the lack of progress being made in the Meyiwa murder case. No arrests have been made two years after the football star was gunned down at his girlfriend Kelly Khumalo's family home in Vosloorus on the east rand. Six months ago, the Hawks described a lack of evidence as the reason behind the delays in arrests. According to major general Prince Mokotedi, the Hawks have questioned nearly 60 people in connection to Meyiwa's murder.